Dataset: (Prosper Loan Data)¶

project 3: Exploratory Data Analysis¶

By: Thomas Oluwasegun Olubunmi¶

Data Source¶

https://s3.amazonaws.com/udacity-hosted-downloads/ud651/prosperLoanData.csv

Introduction¶

Loan Data from Prosper: This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others. The objectives of this project are to summarize the characteristics of features that have effect on the loan status and to get some ideas about the relationships among multiple features using summary statistics and data visualizations.

Research Question:¶

  1. What is the highest proportion of income range of the borrower?
  2. Which credit grade is the most common among the people taking loan?
  3. Is there any relationship between interest rate and credit grade?
  4. How does monthly loan payment affect the score of loan takers?
  5. How does credit rate, monthly loan payment affect borrower APR?

Features of interest¶

Variable Description
ProsperScore Risk Factor score from 1 to 10. 10 being least risky
EmploymentStatus Current type of employment
EmploymentStatusDuration How long the employee has been employed
DebtToIncomeRatio The debt to income ratio of the borrower at the time the credit profile was pulled
StatedMonthlyIncome Monthly income of the borrower
Occupation Occupation of borrower at the time of listing
IsBorrowerHomeowner Does the borrower owns house at the time of listing (True & False)
IncomeRange The income range of the borrower at the time the listing was created
IncomeVerifiable If the income of the borrower is verifiable at the time of listing (True & False)
BorrowerAPR The Borrower’s Annual Percentage Rate (APR) for the loan
BorrowerRate The Borrower’s interest rate for this loan
LoanStatus Current status of the loan like chargedoff, completed, defauted etc…
CreditGrade The Credit rating that was assigned at the time the listing went live
MonthlyLoanPayment Monthly loan payment amount

Univariate Exploration¶

In [54]:
# create a wrange function
def wrangle(filepath):
    # Read csv file
    df = pd.read_csv(filepath)

    # remove outliers
    low, high = df["StatedMonthlyIncome"].quantile([0.1, 0.9])
    mask = df["StatedMonthlyIncome"].between(low, high)
    df = df[mask]
    
    low, high = df["DebtToIncomeRatio"].quantile([0.1, 0.9])
    mask_d = df["DebtToIncomeRatio"].between(low, high)
    df = df[mask_d]
     # drop NaNs Values
    df = df[ (df["Occupation"] != "Other") & (df["Occupation"] != "Professional")\
             & (~df["Occupation"].isna())]
    df = df[(~df.BorrowerAPR.isna())]
    df = df[(~df.IncomeRange.isna())]
    
    return df
In [55]:
# use the wrangle function to load the data into dataframe
df = wrangle("prosperLoanData.csv")

# Convert ProsperRating and credit grade into ordered categorical types

df['ProsperRating (Alpha)'] = df['ProsperRating (Alpha)'].astype("category")
df['ProsperRating (Alpha)'] = df['ProsperRating (Alpha)'].cat.set_categories(
                                    new_categories = rate_order, ordered = True)

grade_order = ['HR','E','D','C','B','A','AA']
df['CreditGrade'] = df['CreditGrade'].astype("category")
df['CreditGrade'] = df['CreditGrade'].cat.set_categories(
                                    new_categories = rate_order, ordered = True)

# create a function to label axes and set tit
def label(xaxis, yaxis, title):
    """This function set the label axes and title of plots"""
    plt.xlabel(xaxis)
    plt.ylabel(yaxis)
    plt.title(title)

Observation¶

There are a number of features that will produce deeper explanation to the profile of loan borrower. I think the main ones for borrowers are credit score, debt to income ratio, income verifiable, home owners and interest rate. During my analysis and with the help of visualizations, I discovered that home owners tend to pay lower interest rate.

Conclusions¶

In the exploration, I found out that the interest rate is negatively correlated with monthly loan payment and prosper score. The borrower APR also decreases with the increasingly better rating. Borrowers with the best Prosper ratings have the lowest APR. It means that the Prosper rating has a strong effect on borrower APR. But people with lower ratings tend to borrow less money, decreasing APR could encourage them to borrow more. Further more, I discovered that there is low interest rate for higher credit grade and higher interest rate for lower credit grade and on the average, the interest rate for the borrower that are home owners is higher than those that are not

Limitations¶

The Exploratory Data Analysis is a good way to investigate the data using clear and interesting visualizations. However, to make final statement about the relationships among variables we need to conduct statistical test and probably build some predictive models.
